After univariate and multivariate COX proportional risk regression analysis, independent prognostic markers that are still significant are used to calculate risk scores in the training set. Risk score is a linear combination of DNA methylation level and regression coefficient of these markers, representing different risk levels of patients. The formula is as follows:
